title.narrative: Quality Instruction Toward Access and Basic Education Improvement (QITABI)

description.narrative: (Lebanon): The QITABI (my book in Arabic) project aims to improve reading outcomes and provide access to education for vulnerable students, both Lebanese and non-Lebanese, enrolled in public schools. In doing so, USAID helps the national providers of public education sustain reading and access reforms. The Lebanese public education sector suffers from fundamental challenges such as lack of consistent teacher professional development, ineffective monitoring and evaluation systems, scarcity of educational materials and poor access to education especially for Syrian refugees. QITABI is currently implementing a number of reading interventions, teacher training and transportation solutions in a total of 512 public schools across Lebanon. So far, the QITABI program has supported over 116,000 students and 1,700 teachers.
